-- 
Scangroup Climbs for Second Day on Report of Market Share Growth

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-07-18T12:20:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-18/scangroup-climbs-for-second-day-on-report-of-market-share-growth.html
Scangroup Ltd., East Africa’s
biggest marketing and advertising company, gained a second day
after a  Business Daily  report that the company’s market share
increased.  The stock climbed as much as 4 percent to 52.5 shillings
before trading 2 percent higher at 51.50 shillings by the 3 p.m.
close in the capital, Nairobi, Scangroup’s highest level since
July 12.  Scangroup’s market share has grown to 80 percent from 71
percent in September after acquiring rival Ogilvy East Africa
and an increase in advertising expenditure by  Kenya ’s biggest
companies, Business Daily said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
